This move's goal is to fix the weakeness of the d-file and to reinstate the threat on Nc3. However, now the knight would attack the queen when taking on d5, so in some variations it can be of disadvantage. Moreover, it does not do anything to stop the queenside attack of the white (which black did not see). SF suggestion is to play 18. ... Rb8 and if white tries to start the same attack as before 19. a5 h6 20. a6 b5 21. Qxc6 Sg4 can exploits the weakness of the h4 pawn. According to SF5, the game could continue with 22. g3 b4 23. Rd7 Qf6 24. Qxf6 Nxf6 25. Na4 Nxd7 26. Rxd7
